WEBVTT

00:03.069 --> 00:04.570
<i>In the last episode of</i> Soap,

00:04.571 --> 00:06.572
<i>Burt told Sally</i>
<i>he could see her no more.</i>

00:06.573 --> 00:08.574
<i>He's sorry,</i>
<i>but it's the only way.</i>

00:08.575 --> 00:10.576
<i>Sally took it well indeed.</i>

00:10.577 --> 00:12.578
<i>She threatened</i>
<i>to get him some day.</i>

00:12.579 --> 00:15.080
<i>Donohue told Jessica</i>
<i>that Chester died...</i>

00:15.081 --> 00:16.582
<i>on an exploded train,</i>

00:16.583 --> 00:18.083
<i>but Chester's not dead.</i>

00:18.084 --> 00:21.086
<i>He's very alive,</i>
<i>although with a muddled brain.</i>

00:21.087 --> 00:23.589
<i>Jodie's still stunned</i>
<i>that Carol left him.</i>

00:23.590 --> 00:25.090
<i>He's been in a lot of pain.</i>

00:25.091 --> 00:27.092
<i>And Danny's vowed to get the men</i>

00:27.093 --> 00:28.594
<i>who killed his precious Elaine.</i>

00:28.595 --> 00:30.095
<i>Confused?</i>

00:30.096 --> 00:32.098
<i>You won't be after</i>
<i>tonight's episode of...</i> Soap

00:38.605 --> 00:40.606
<i>This is the story</i>
<i>of two sisters,</i>

00:40.607 --> 00:43.108
<i>Jessica Tate</i>

00:43.109 --> 00:45.110
<i>and Mary Campbell.</i>

00:45.111 --> 00:48.614
<i>These are the Tates,</i>

00:48.615 --> 00:52.618
<i>and these are the Campbells.</i>

00:52.619 --> 00:54.621
<i>And this is</i> Soap.

