19:50.255 --> 19:53.758
♪ Bringing in The sheaves ♪

19:53.759 --> 19:54.759
Hey, buddy.

19:54.760 --> 19:58.763
What the hell is a sheaf anyway?

19:58.764 --> 19:59.764
Hey, buddy, I'm talking to you.

19:59.765 --> 20:01.766
What?

20:01.767 --> 20:03.768
What is a sheaf?

20:03.769 --> 20:05.770
It's a quantity
of cereal grasses

20:05.771 --> 20:06.771
bound together.

20:06.772 --> 20:08.272
Ah.

20:08.273 --> 20:11.275
Tell me, why do we want
to bring them in? Well, uh...

20:11.276 --> 20:13.277
Uh, it's because of the harvest.

20:13.278 --> 20:15.780
Uh, we plant in the spring,

20:15.781 --> 20:16.781
and we harvest...

20:16.782 --> 20:18.783
Uh, could you try
not touching me

20:18.784 --> 20:20.284
quite so much?

20:20.285 --> 20:21.786
What's the matter?
You don't like to be touched?

20:21.787 --> 20:22.787
Well, it's a...

20:22.788 --> 20:24.789
Hey, fellas!

20:24.790 --> 20:26.290
Fancy Pants here
don't like to be touched.

20:26.291 --> 20:27.792
Oh, well, no, it's...

20:27.793 --> 20:28.793
MEN: Whoo! MEN: Whoo!

20:28.794 --> 20:29.794
Oh. Ah!

20:29.795 --> 20:31.295
It's just that, ah...

20:31.296 --> 20:33.297
Well, you see, I, uh,
don't really belong here.

20:33.298 --> 20:34.799
I'm not really a bum.

20:34.800 --> 20:36.300
You calling us bums?

20:36.301 --> 20:37.802
Oh, no. Please.

20:37.803 --> 20:38.803
Please don't be offended.

20:38.804 --> 20:40.304
I like bums.

20:40.305 --> 20:41.806
Some of my best friends are...

20:41.807 --> 20:43.308
filthy and disgusting.

20:45.310 --> 20:46.310
All right...

20:46.311 --> 20:48.312
Ah, split pea!

20:48.313 --> 20:49.814
I love split pea.

20:57.322 --> 20:58.322
Pass the bread plate.

20:58.323 --> 21:00.324
Are we grabbing?
Is that it?

21:00.325 --> 21:01.325
Give me the bread.

21:01.326 --> 21:02.827
Wait.

21:02.828 --> 21:04.829
How do I know I like split pea?

21:04.830 --> 21:05.830
Hey.

21:05.831 --> 21:06.831
I remember.
That's how I know.

21:06.832 --> 21:07.832
I remember.

21:07.833 --> 21:08.833
Pass the plate.

21:08.834 --> 21:09.834
Come on, pass the plate.

21:09.835 --> 21:11.836
Please.

21:11.837 --> 21:13.337
You are beginning to pester me.

21:13.338 --> 21:16.341
Pester...

21:20.846 --> 21:22.346
Nester...

21:22.347 --> 21:23.848
Mester...

21:23.849 --> 21:25.850
Lester! That's it!

21:25.851 --> 21:26.851
Pass the plate.

21:26.852 --> 21:30.354
Oh! Pl... Pa...

21:30.355 --> 21:32.857
I'm Lester Pate!

21:32.858 --> 21:34.358
Pleased to meet you.

21:34.359 --> 21:35.860
Now, do you pass me the bread,

21:35.861 --> 21:37.361
or do I tear off your head?

21:37.362 --> 21:39.864
Oh, sir, you've
helped me to remember.

21:39.865 --> 21:40.865
How could I ever repay you?

21:40.866 --> 21:41.866
Bread.

21:41.867 --> 21:43.367
Take the bread.

21:43.368 --> 21:44.869
Take my soup.

21:44.870 --> 21:45.870
I remember. Oh...

21:45.871 --> 21:48.372
and I owe it all to you.

21:48.373 --> 21:50.374
You helped me gain
my true self again.

21:50.375 --> 21:51.876
Goodbye.

21:53.879 --> 21:54.879
Where you going?

21:54.880 --> 21:56.881
Home, to my family.

21:56.882 --> 21:58.382
Oh, yeah? Where do they live?

21:58.383 --> 22:00.384
I don't know.

22:00.385 --> 22:02.386
But they're out there somewhere.

22:02.387 --> 22:03.888
Somewhere,

22:03.889 --> 22:05.890
there's a family of Pates
waiting for their Lester,

22:05.891 --> 22:07.391
and I'll find them.

22:07.392 --> 22:10.394
If I have to look in every city,
in every town, I'll find them,

22:10.395 --> 22:12.897
because when Lester Pate gets it
into his head to do something,

22:12.898 --> 22:14.398
he does it,

22:14.399 --> 22:17.902
because that's the kind of stuff
we Pates are made of.

22:17.903 --> 22:18.904
I think.

